      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so u mentioned those \"incentives\" for growth vs the \"loopholes\" for high earners. between the two, is there a consensus in the actual economic literature on which effect is likely to be more dominant? like, do most mainstream economists see this as a net positive for inequality or is the widening gap the more \"settled\" prediction?",
